Task 3: Correlation between news sentiment and stock movement
Objective: Quantify the relationship between financial news sentiment and daily stock price returns using statistical methods.

Instructions:

Date Alignment
Normalize timestamps across both datasets so that news items are matched to the corresponding stock trading day
Handle edge cases: articles published on weekends or holidays should be aligned to the next trading day
Sentiment Analysis
Apply a sentiment analysis tool to assign a numerical sentiment score to each headline
Recommended tools: TextBlob, NLTK VADER
Justify your tool selection briefly in your report
Calculate Daily Stock Returns
Compute daily percentage change in closing prices: (Close*t - Close*{t-1}) / Close\_{t-1} \* 100
Aggregate and Correlate
If multiple articles are published on the same day for the same stock, compute the average daily sentiment score
Calculate the Pearson correlation coefficient between average daily sentiment scores and daily stock returns
Visualize the relationship with a scatter plot and annotate the correlation value
Classify each day as positive, neutral, or negative based on its average sentiment score, then plot the average daily return per category as a bar chart
Interpret Results
Discuss the strength and direction of the correlation
Note any limitations of the approach (e.g., lag effects, confounding factors)
